The paper focuses on compressed sensing and image processing, which are core topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The use of sparsity and transform domains also suggests a possible connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the application to MRI specifically may suggest a connection to Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
